s, Photos, on popcorn.oneindia.in|work=FilmiBeat}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Ready (2011 film)|Ready]]''\n| Sanjana Singh / Pooja Malhotra\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[Hindi]] \n|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|title=Ready (2011)|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/cast/id/525563|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=18 May 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2012\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Housefull 2]]''\n| Heena\n|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|title=Housefull 2 (2012)|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/cast/id/542290|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=18 May 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Bol Bachchan]]''\n| Sania Ali / Sania Bachchan / Apeksha\n|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|title=Bol Bachchan (2012)|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/cast/id/545484|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=18 May 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Khiladi 786]]''\n| Indu Tendulkar\n|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|title=Khiladi 786 (2012)|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/cast/id/548099|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=18 May 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[All Is Well (2015 film)|All Is Well]]''\n| Nimmi\n| \n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|title=All Is Well (2014)|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/cast/id/622498|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=18 May 2014}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|India|Bollywood}}\n* [[List of Indian film actresses]]\n{{Clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Asin (actress)}}\n* {{IMDb name|id=1821791|name=Asin}}\n* {{Instagram|simply.asin |Asin}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Awards for Asin\n| list1=\n{{FilmfareTamilBestActress}}\n{{FilmfareTeluguBestActress}}\n{{FilmfareAwardBestFemaleDebut}}\n{{IIFAAwardBestFemaleDebut}}\n{{ScreenAwardBestFemaleDebut}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Asin}}\n[[Category:Actresses from Kochi]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Malayalam cinema]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Telugu cinema]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Hindi cinema]]\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Filmfare Awards South winners]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Tamil cinema]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Kalaimamani Award]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian actresses]]\n[[Category:Indian film actresses]]\n[[Category:International Tamil Film Award winners]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Malayalam television]]\n[[Category:Indian television actresses]]\n[[Category:Syro-Malabar Catholics]]\n", "text_old": "{{about|the Indian actress Asin Thottumkal|other uses|Asin (disambiguation)}}\n{{pp-pc1}}\n{{short description|Indian actress}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2016}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Asin Thottumkal\n| image              = Asin 'Bol Bachchan' team on the sets of Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah 03.jpg\n| caption            = Asin at Bol Bachchan press meet.\n| native_name_lang   = \n| birth_name         = Asin Thottumkal\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1985|10|26}}<ref name=\"only 23\">{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-04-21/news-interviews/28058815_1_joseph-thottumkal-asin-age-factor|title=I am only 23: Asin|accessdate=4 August 2013|date=21 April 2009|newspaper=The Times of India}}</ref><ref name=\"hide\">{{cite news|last=Dasgupta|first=Priyanka|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-10-26/news-interviews/28234079_1_asin-movie-business-childhood-friends|title=I can't hide my age: Asin|accessdate=4 August 2013|date=26 October 2010|newspaper=The Times of India}}</ref><ref name=\"working birthday\">{{cite news|last=Singh|first=Prashant|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Tabloid/Asin-Thottumkal-has-a-working-birthday-turns-26-on-sets/Article1-950368.aspx|title=Asin Thottumkal has a working birthday, turns 26 on sets|accessdate=4 August 2013|date=26 October 2012|newspaper=Hindustan Times}}</ref>\n| birth_place        = [[Kochi]], [[Kerala]], [[India]]\n| residence          = [[Kochi]], [[India]]<ref>{{cite news|title=No visits to Dad: Micromax boss Rahul Sharma has to stay away from wife Asin, 2-yr-old due to Delhi's pollution woes|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/no-visits-to-dad-micromax-boss-rahul-sharma-has-to-stay-away-from-wife-asin-2-yr-old-due-to-delhis-pollution-woes/articleshow/72814698.cms|date=17 December 2019|newspaper=[[The Economic Times]]}}</ref>\n| nationality        = [[Indian People|Indian]]\n| occupation         = Actress, Model, Dancer\n| years_active       = 2001\u20132015\n| agent              = \n| notable_works      = \n| style              = \n| home_town          = [[Kochi]], [[Kerala]], India\n| net_worth          = \n| height             = \n| spouse             = {{married| [[Rahul Sharma (businessman)|Rahul Sharma]]|2016}}\n| children           = 1 (Arin)<ref name=\"ndtv2\"/>\n| parents            = \n| awards             = {{unbulleted list|[[Kalaimamani]]|[[Filmfare Awards]]}}\n| signature          = \n| signature_size     = \n| signature_alt      = \n| footnotes          = \n| related family     = \n}}\n\n'''Asin Thottumkal''' (born 26 October 1985),<ref name=\"only 23\"/><ref name=\"hide\"/><ref name=\"working birthday\"/> known [[Mononymous person|mononymously]] as '''Asin''', is a former [[Indian people|Indian]] actress who mostly appeared in [[Tamil language|Tamil]] films. She also appeared in lead roles in  [[Hindi]], [[Telugu language|Telugu]] and [[Malayalam]] films. She is a trained [[Bharathanatyam]] dancer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Asins-classical-avataar/articleshow/5115585.cms|title=Asin\u2019s classical avataar|publisher=TOI (Times Of India)|date=13 October 2009}}</ref> She has received three [[Filmfare Awards]]. She began her acting career in the [[South Indian film industry]], but later shifted her focus to [[Bollywood]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-02-17/news-interviews/37133521_1_lucky-mascot-ghajini-actors |title=I want to work with younger actors of my generation: Asin |work=The Times of India |date=17 February 2013 |accessdate=2 March 2013}}</ref> She speaks eight languages,<ref name=\"Desimartini.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.desimartini.com/news/telugu/asin-busy-learning-german/article4973.htm|title=Asin busy in learning German|date=7 June 2013|work=Desimartini.com|publisher=Top Movies Entertainment Ltd|accessdate=28 October 2014}}</ref> and [[Dubbing (filmmaking)|dubs]] her own films.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://meencurry.com/biography-asin-thottumkal/|title=Biography: Asin Thottumkal {{!}} Meen Curry|website=meencurry.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-02-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170220181557/http://meencurry.com/biography-asin-thottumkal/|archive-date=20 February 2017|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"asinonline1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.asinonline.com/images/press/english/asin-new-indian.jpg |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004215724/http://www.asinonline.com/images/press/english/asin-new-indian.jpg |url-status=dead |archive-date=4 October 2013 |title=Asin speaks Hindi |publisher=asinonline.com |accessdate=2 June 2013 }}</ref> She is the only [[Malayali]] actress, other than [[Padmini (actress)|Padmini]], to have [[Dubbing (filmmaking)|dubbed]] in her own voice for all her films, irrespective of language.<ref name=\"asinonline1\"/> Asin has been referred to as the \"Queen of [[Kollywood]]\" by online portals in 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/tamil/news/2007/top-five-heroines-2007-311207.html|title=Top 5 heroines of the year 2007: Asin easily topples all!|work=www.filmibeat.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/asin-s-birthday-bash-news-tamil-kkfuySaicca.html|title=Asin`s birthday bash!|work=Sify}}</ref> She is a member of the [[Bollywood 100 Crore Club]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/asin-kareena-rule-bollywood-s-100-cr-club-news-bollywood-mh4ub0fddab.html|title=Asin & Kareena rule Bollywood`s 100 Cr club!|work=Sify}}</ref>\n\nMaking her acting debut with [[Sathyan Anthikkad]]'s [[Malayalam film]] ''[[Narendran Makan Jayakanthan Vaka]]'' (2001), Asin had her first commercial success with the [[Telugu language|Telugu]] film ''[[Amma Nanna O Tamila Ammayi]]'' in 2003, and won a [[Filmfare Best Actress Award (Telugu)|Filmfare Best Telugu Actress Award]] for the film. ''[[M. Kumaran S/O Mahalakshmi]]'' (2004) was her debut in [[Tamil language|Tamil]] and a huge success. She received her [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress \u2013 Tamil|Filmfare Best Tamil Actress Award]] for her most noted critically acclaimed performance in her third Tamil film, ''[[Ghajini (2005 film)|Ghajini]]'' (2005). She then played the lead female roles in many successful films, the most notable being the action ''[[Sivakasi (film)|Sivakasi]]'' (2005), the dramatic thriller ''[[Varalaru]]'' (2006), the action thriller ''[[Pokkiri]]'' (2007), the romantic drama ''[[Vel (film)|Vel]]'' (2008) and ''[[Dasavathaaram]]'' (2008), hence established herself as the leading actress of Tamil cinema and was also honoured by the Tamil Nadu government with the [[Kalaimamani]] award for her excellence in the field of art and literature.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.hindu.com/2009/11/29/stories/2009112960210600.htm | location=Chennai, India | work=The Hindu | title=Kalaimamani awards presented to 70 persons | date=29 November 2009}}</ref> In 2013, Asin was conferred with the [[2nd South Indian International Movie Awards#Generation Next Awards|Pride of South Indian Cinema]] award at SIIMA for her contribution to Tamil cinema.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/5511|title=Asin bags the Pride of South Indian Cinema Award - Latest Movie Features - Bollywood Hungama|author=Bollywood Hungama|work=bollywoodhungama.com}}</ref>\n\nIn late 2008, Asin made her debut in the [[Bollywood]] film ''[[Ghajini (2008 film)|Ghajini]]'' (2008), opposite [[Aamir Khan]], which was the first Bollywood film to have collected more than {{INR}}1&nbsp;billion in the domestic box office, subsequently collecting {{INRConvert|1.9|b}} worldwide. Asin won the [[Filmfare Best Female Debut Award]] and many accolades for Ghajini. 2011 marked the most successful phase of Asin's Bollywood career, as she starred in [[Anees Bazmee]]'s [[romantic comedy]] ''[[Ready (2011 film)|Ready]]'', in which she co-starred alongside [[Salman Khan]]. The film was a major hit at the box office, collecting {{INRConvert|1.84|b}} worldwide.<ref>[http://boxofficeindia.com/arounddetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=3997&nCat== Top Worldwide Grossers ALL TIME:  100 Crore] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130523013047/http://boxofficeindia.com/arounddetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=3997&nCat=%3D |date=23 May 2013 }}. Box Office India (3 February 2012). Retrieved 10 July 2012.</ref> In 2012, Asin first starred in [[Sajid Khan]]'s multistarrer ''[[Housefull 2]]'', which collected more than {{INR}}1&nbsp;billion. She then featured in ''[[Bol Bachchan]]'' and ''[[Khiladi 786]]'', which were also commercially successful with both grossing over {{INR}}1&nbsp;billion.\n\n==Early life==\n[[File:Asin at Riteish Deshmukh and Genelia D'Souza's wedding at Grand Hyatt.jpg|thumb|right|150px|Asin at a wedding]]\nAsin was born in [[Kochi]] in [[Kerala]] in a [[Malayali]] [[Syro-Malabar Catholic]] family.<ref name=\"telegraphindia1\">{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1060514/asp/look/story_6217361.asp |title=Look |work=The Telegraph |date=14 May 2006 |accessdate=2 March 2013 |location=Calcutta, India}}</ref> Her father Joseph Thottumkal is an Ex-CBI officer and later managed several businesses. Her mother Seline Thottumkal, who moved from Kochi to [[Chennai]] and then to [[Mumbai]] to live with her daughter, is a surgeon. According to custom, Asin was to be named Mary, after her paternal grandmother. Asin's father however, named her Asin as the name had a beautiful meaning.<ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-06-14/did-you-know-/32234556_1_asin-dam-meaning/ Asin was supposed to be named as Mary]. ''The Times of India''. (14 June 2012). Retrieved 10 July 2012.</ref> Asin has quoted that her name means \"pure and without blemish\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/did-you-know-/Asins-another-name/articleshow/47213945.cms|title=Asin's another name!}}</ref> She states that the 'A' in her name is from [[Sanskrit]] meaning \"without\", and \"sin\" from English.<ref name=\"name\">{{cite news|author=Ahmed, afsana|work=[[The Times of India]]|title=Salman's very supportive: Asin|date=11 May 2009|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-05-11/news-interviews/28193770_1_19th-step-asin-thottumkal-tadanobu-asano |accessdate=5 August 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.hindu.com/2009/03/09/stories/2009030959600300.htm | location=Chennai, India | work=The Hindu | title=A surprise step, an award-winning debut | date=9 March 2009}}</ref>\n\nShe attended [[Navy Children School|Naval Public School]] from [[Kindergarten#India|LKG]] through X standard.<ref name = \"TOI\">{{cite news| url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-11-10/news-interviews/35015795_1_aamir-khan-ghajini-crore-films| work=The Times of India | title=I am quite like Aamir: Asin | date=10 November 2012| accessdate = 10 November 2012}}</ref> She then attended St. Teresa's School in Kochi for her [[Kerala Higher Secondary Examination Board]] (Plus Two) Education. After that, she attended [[St. Teresa's College]] in Kochi, a college affiliated with [[Mahatma Gandhi University, Kerala|MG University]], where she graduated with a [[Bachelor of Arts]] degree in [[English Literature]].<ref>{{cite web|title=I have seen enough success before to not get carried away|url=http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2009/mar/19slide2-verve-cover-girl-asin.htm|work=Rediff|accessdate=5 January 2011}} {{failed verification|date=October 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\n===Early work (2001\u201304)===\n[[File:Asin08.jpg|right|thumb|Asin with the cast and crew of ''[[Ghajini (2008 film)|Ghajini]]'' celebrating the film's worldwide gross of 200 crores]]\nAsin's first assignment was an advertisement for [[Loop Mobile|BPL Mobile]]. She debuted in the [[Malayalam]] film ''[[Narendran Makan Jayakanthan Vaka]]'' in 2001, at the age of 15. After taking a year out to pursue her education, Asin returned with her breakthrough film as an actress, ''[[Amma Nanna O Tamila Ammayi]]'' opposite [[Ravi Teja]], portraying a [[Tamil people|Tamil]] girl in her first [[Telugu language]] film, which subsequently fetched her the [[Filmfare Best Actress Award (Telugu)|Telugu Filmfare Award for Best Actress]].<ref name=\"awards\">{{cite web|author=Thottumkal, Asin|publisher=AsinOnline.com|title=Awards|date=24 December 2008|url=http://www.asinonline.com/awards.htm|accessdate=24 December 2008}}</ref> In the same year she won the [[Santosham Best Actress Award]] for her performance alongside [[Akkineni Nagarjuna]] in her second Telugu film ''[[Shivamani (film)|Shivamani]]''.<ref name=\"awards\"/> Her following two [[Telugu language|Telugu]] films ''[[Lakshmi Narasimha]]'' and ''[[Gharshana]]'', both portrayed Asin as the love interest for police officers and both were successful ventures.\n\nAsin's first [[Tamil language]] film was ''[[M. Kumaran S/O Mahalakshmi]]'', in which she co-starred with [[Jayam Ravi]]. Asin reprised her role from her film ''Amma Nanna O Tamila Ammayi'' for the remake, which saw her portraying a [[Malayali]] girl instead of the Tamil girl in the original. The movie subsequently went on to super-hit in [[Tamil cinema]] during 2004, introducing Asin to [[Tamil film industry]].<ref name=\"mkumaran\">{{cite web|author=Radhakrishnan, Mathangi |publisher=MusicIndiaOnline |title='M. Kumaran...' rules the Tamil box office |date=15 October 2004 |url=http://www.musicindiaonline.com/n/i/tamil/903/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070224041036/http://www.musicindiaonline.com/n/i/tamil/903/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=24 February 2007 |accessdate=24 December 2008 }}</ref> After a brief return to Telugu films, to do ''[[Chakram (2005 film)|Chakram]]'', she appeared in ''[[Ullam Ketkumae]]''.<ref name=\"chakram\">{{cite news|author=Narasimhan, ML|work=[[The Hindu]]|title=Dubbed films rule yet again |date=30 December 2005|url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2005/12/30/stories/2005123002160100.htm|accessdate=24 December 2008|location=Chennai, India}}</ref> The film, initially launched in 2002, was supposed to be her debut as a lead heroine, is a college love story, directed by [[Jeeva (director)|Jeeva]], which was long-delayed but eventually became a successful venture at the box office, creating wider opportunities for her and the rest of the cast.<ref name=\"uk\">{{cite web|author=Shivram, Prasanna|work=[[The Hindu]]|title=Jeeva's lyrical frames |date=13 July 2007|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/life/2007/07/13/stories/2007071350040200.htm|accessdate=24 December 2008}}</ref>\n\n===Kollywood breakthrough and stardom (2005\u201307)===\nAfter the release of ''Ullam Ketkumae'', Asin was cited as a leading heroine of the Tamil film industry after starring in blockbuster films such as ''[[Ghajini (2005 film)|Ghajini]]'', ''[[Sivakasi (film)|Sivakasi]]'', ''[[Varalaru]]'' and ''[[Pokkiri]]'' respectively.<ref name=\"fourbig\">{{cite news|author=Kamath, Sudhish|work=[[The Hindu]]|title=Asin turns out to be the brightest sparkler this year|date=1 November 2005|url=http://www.hindu.com/2005/11/01/stories/2005110117190200.htm|accessdate=24 December 2008|location=Chennai, India}}</ref> The film which provided the breakthrough for Asin was ''[[Ghajini (2005 film)|Ghajini]]''. The film, co-starring [[Suriya (actor)|Surya]], directed by [[A.R. Murugadoss]], earned her the [[Filmfare Best Actress Award (Tamil)|Tamil Filmfare Award for Best Actress]]. Her role was that of a vivacious young model named Kalpana. [[Sify]].com praised her portrayal as \"magical\", describing her character as a \"lovable chatterbox\", played with \"sheer ability in the romantic interludes, the poignant and heartfelt scenes when she rescues minor girls from villains and her gory end are touching\".<ref name=\"sifykalapna\">{{cite web|publisher=[[Sify]]|title=Ghajini|date=27 September 2005|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/review.php?id=13952885&ctid=5&cid=2429|accessdate=23 December 2008}}</ref> On the following [[Diwali]] in 2005, Asin had two releases, ''[[Sivakasi (film)|Sivakasi]]'' and ''[[Majaa]]''. Despite the latter becoming an average grosser, the former went on to be a successful venture at the box office.<ref name=\"sivakasi\">{{cite news|author=Rangarajan, Malathi|work=[[The Hindu]]|title=With the formula intact |date=11 November 2005|url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2005/11/11/stories/2005111100180200.htm|accessdate=24 December 2008|location=Chennai, India}}</ref><ref name=\"majaa\">{{cite web|author=Ashok Kumar, SR|work=[[The Hindu]]|title=Where is the entertainment? |date=4 November 2005|url=http://www.hindujobs.com/thehindu/fr/2005/11/04/stories/2005110402340200.htm|accessdate=24 December 2008}}</ref>\n\nThe following year, her long-delayed venture ''[[Varalaru (film)|Varalaru]]'' opposite [[Ajith Kumar]] also succeeded at the box office, and The Hindu said she \"looks lustrous and sails through her role smoothly\".<ref name=\"Varalaru\">{{cite news|author=Rangarajan, Malathi|work=[[The Hindu]]|title=In the race, surely&nbsp;\u2014 Varalaaru |date=27 October 2006|url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2006/10/27/stories/2006102700060200.htm|accessdate=24 December 2008|location=Chennai, India}}</ref> Asin appeared in [[Pawan Kalyan]]'s ''[[Annavaram]]'', another successful venture, which was a remake of [[Thirupaachi]].<ref name=\"Annavaram\">{{cite web|author=Vardhan, Adithya|publisher=[[Rediff]]|title=Annavaram is paisa vasool|date=2 January 2007|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2007/jan/02anna.htm|accessdate=24 December 2008}}</ref> In January 2007, Asin appeared opposite Ajith Kumar and Vijay in two different films, ''[[Aalwar]]'' and ''[[Pokkiri]]'', with the latter becoming a success, whilst ''Aalwar'' became a failure. Though Asin's role in ''Aalwar'' was criticised, her performance in ''Pokkiri'' was lauded by critics.<ref name=\"LAalwarl\">{{cite web|author=Mohan, Piraba|publisher=Behindwoods|title=Aalwar: Ajith is the saving grace|date=14 January 2007|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-articles/movies-05/aalwar-review.html|accessdate=24 December 2008}}</ref><ref name=\"LPokkiri\">{{cite web|author=Bhaskar, Shweta|publisher=[[Rediff]]|title=Pokkiri: Watch only for Vijay, Asin|date=15 January 2007|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2007/jan/15sspokkiri.htm|accessdate=24 December 2008}}</ref> Her final project of the year was opposite Surya, in [[Hari (director)|Hari's]] ''[[Vel (film)|Vel]]'', which had a Diwali 2007 release, subsequently becoming her third successful film which released during the Diwali season in three years. Asin, who portrayed a [[TV anchor]], was appreciated for her role in the film.<ref name=\"LondonVel\">{{cite web|author=Hari, TSV|publisher=[[Rediff]]|title=Vel is slick and neat|date=8 November 2007|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2007/nov/08vel.htm|accessdate=24 December 2008}}</ref>\n\n===Bollywood debut (2008\u201310)===\n[[File:Asin Thottumkal.jpg|thumb|250px|left|150px|Asin in 2010]]\nAsin appeared in her first dual role in [[K. S. Ravikumar]]'s ''[[Dasavathaaram]]'' opposite [[Kamal Haasan]], who portrayed ten roles. The film had been under production since September 2006. Despite being overshadowed by Haasan's ten roles, Asin's portrayals in the film were praised as her \"best-to-date\", with one of her roles being that of a [[Vaishnavite]] in 12th century [[Tamil Nadu]]; whilst the other character was a [[Brahmin]] girl from [[Chidambaram]], for which she won her first [[ITFA Best Actress Award]].<ref name=\"Dasavtharamperf\">{{cite web|author=Vijayasarathy, R. G.|publisher=[[Rediff]]|title=Dasavathaaram is spectacular|date=13 June 2008|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2008/jun/13dasa.htm|accessdate=24 December 2008}}</ref> ''Dasavathaaram'' subsequently went on to become one of the blockbusters.<ref name=\"Dasavtharamblockbuster\">{{cite web|work=[[The Times (South Africa)|The Times]]|title=Kamalhassan's new blockbuster hit is setting records worldwide|date=29 June 2008|url=http://www.thetimes.co.za/Entertainment/Article.aspx?id=792296|accessdate=24 December 2008}}</ref>\n\nSince establishing herself as the leading actress in South India, Asin opted to move into [[Bollywood]]. Her first film ''[[Ghajini (2008 film)|Ghajini]]'', opposite [[Aamir Khan]], was the remake of her breakthrough film of the same name. Upon release, the film garnered positive reactions from critics and masses alike, with Asin being singled out for her \"fabulous\" portrayal. Noted critic [[Taran Adarsh]] described her Hindi debut as \"fabulous\" and that \"to share the screen space with an actor of the stature of Aamir Khan and yet remain in your memory even after the show has ended is no cakewalk. She looks fresh and photogenic and acts her part brilliantly, giving Asin's performance a positive outlook.\"<ref name=\"GhajiniHindi\">{{cite web|author=Adarsh, Taran|publisher=[[Sify]]|title=Review: Ghajini has blockbuster written all over it|date=23 December 2008|url=http://sify.com/movies/bollywood/review.php?id=14824058&ctid=5&cid=2425|accessdate=23 December 2008|authorlink=Taran Adarsh}}</ref>\n\n''Ghajini'' became the highest grossing Bollywood film of 2008 and the sixth [[List of highest-grossing Bollywood films|highest-grossing Bollywood film]] of all time according to net collections.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=127&catName=MjAwMC0yMDA5|title=Top Lifetime Grossers 2000\u20132009 (Figures in Ind Rs)|publisher=Box-Office-India}}</ref> Asin later appeared in [[Vipul Shah]]'s ''[[London Dreams]]'', alongside [[Salman Khan]] and [[Ajay Devgn]], in which she played a south Indian girl, Priya, who is emotional but strong willed and an ambitious dancer at the same time.<ref name=\"LondonDreamsHindi\">{{cite web|author=Jha, Subhash. K|publisher=[[NDTV]]|title=Asin to croon for London Dreams|date=10 December 2008|url=http://music.ndtv.com/story.asp?id=ENTEN20080075988|accessdate=24 December 2008}}</ref><ref name=\"InternationalAsin\">{{cite web|author=IndiaGlitz|publisher=IndiaGlitz|title=Asin's encore with Kamal Hassan|date=17 January 2009|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/hindi/article/44351.html|accessdate=17 January 2009}}</ref> The film received mixed reviews from critics.\n\nHer first film of 2011 was ''[[Kaavalan]]'', which released on 15 January 2011. The film was a critical and commercial success.<ref>{{cite web\n | url        = http://www.sify.com/movies/vijay-s-kaavalan-is-a-moridate%20hits-news-tamil-lbzkgaadefh.html\n | title      = Vijay's Kaavalan is a hit!\n | publisher  = Sify\n | accessdate = 26 January 2011\n}}</ref> ''Behindwoods'' review of the film praised her performance: \"Asin, in Tamil for the first time after ''Dasavatharam'', convinces us with her portrayal. The chemistry of the lead pair has worked out well; especially the portions w things that ultimately result in love\". The chemistry between [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]] and Asin worked out well and was appreciated. Asin went on to win the SIIMA Award for Best Actress for this film. The film also includes Vadivelu as the comedian along with [[Mithra Kurian]], [[Roja (actress)|Roja]] and [[Rajkiran]] playing supporting roles.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-reviews/reviews-2/kavalan-movie-review.html |title=Vijay (re)turns romantic! Feel good&nbsp;\u2013 Feel emotional |publisher=Behindwoods |accessdate=23 March 2011}}</ref>\n\n===Final work (2011\u201315)===\n[[File:Asin housefull 2 party.jpg|thumb|right|150px|Asin at ''[[Housefull 2]]'' success party at [[Akshay Kumar]]'s house, 2012]]\n\nHer next movie with Salman Khan, ''[[Ready (2011 film)|Ready]]'', was released on 3 June 2011 to mixed reviews.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ibosnetwork.com/newsmanager/templates/template1.aspx?a=22264&z=9 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120710060504/http://ibosnetwork.com/newsmanager/templates/template1.aspx?a=22264&z=9 |url-status=dead |archive-date=10 July 2012 |title=Box Office: Ready opens to good opening with mixed response |publisher=ibosnetwork |accessdate=4 June 2011 }}</ref> Critics praised the chemistry between Salman and Asin.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/hindi/review/12984.html |title=Ready Movie Review |publisher=Behindwoods |accessdate=5 June 2011}}</ref> Upon release, ''Ready'' became the second highest weekend grossing Bollywood film, after ''[[Dabangg]]''<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-06-07/box-office/29629146_1_multiplexes-small-budget-releases-single-screen|title=Ready is second to Dabangg|work= The Times of India|accessdate=7 June 2011|date=7 June 2011}}</ref> and went on to become the fifth film in Bollywood history to cross the coveted {{INRConvert|1|b}} mark in the domestic market.\n\nIn 2012, she first appeared alongside [[Akshay Kumar]] in [[Sajid Khan]]'s multistarrer comedy ''[[Housefull 2]]''. Though it received a mixed critical reception,<ref>{{cite web|title=Housefull 2 gets average reviews from film critics|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/bollywood/features/2012/housefull-2-rave-reviews-critics-verdict-090412.html|accessdate=1 April 2013}}</ref> it was a major commercial success.<ref>{{cite web|title=Top Ten 2012 Lifetime Grossers |url=http://boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=5038&nCat= |publisher=Box Office India |accessdate=1 April 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121102181249/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=5038&nCat= |archivedate=2 November 2012 }}</ref> Asin generally received favourable reviews for her performance, with Adarsh stating that \"[a]mongst the female leads, Asin has the meatiest role and gives a decent account of herself.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Adarsh|first=Taran|title=Housefull 2 Movie Review (2012)|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/542290|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=1 April 2013}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 July 2012, [[Rohit Shetty]]'s ''[[Bol Bachchan]]'', alongside [[Ajay Devgn]] and [[Abhishek Bachchan]], released with mixed reviews with the critics praising the performances of Asin, Ajay Devgn, and Abhishek Bachchan. [[Taran Adarsh]] from Bollywood Hungama, who praised Asin's performance stated: \"Asin does well, though her screen time is limited. Nonetheless, her amiable looks and stimulating smile add to her charisma!!.\"<ref>[http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/545484 Bol Bachchan (2012) | Hindi Movie Critic Review By Taran Adarsh]. Bollywood Hungama. Retrieved 10 July 2012.</ref> While the reviewer from Behindwoods quoted: \"There is a small surprise with regards to Asin's role. She is the romantic interest of Ajay and looks serene and absolutely cute.\"<ref>[http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-reviews/reviews-2/jul-12-01/bol-bachchan-review.html Bol Bachchan Review]. Behindwoods.com. Retrieved 10 July 2012.</ref> The movie is now declared a super hit.<ref name=\"articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com\">{{cite news|author=Bharti Dubey |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-07-13/box-office/32662398_1_box-office-bol-bachchan-net-box |title=Bol Bachchan's business going strong at box office |work=The Times of India |date=13 July 2012 |accessdate=26 October 2012}}</ref>\n\n''[[Khiladi 786]]'', in which she reunited with her ''[[Housefull 2]]'' costar, [[Akshay Kumar]], released on 7 December 2012 to mixed reviews, but was strong at the box office and eventually became a commercially successful venture.<ref name=\"hindustantimes.com\">[http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/BO-Report-Akshay-Kumar-s-Khiladi-786-passes-the-test/Article1-971496.aspx BO Report: Akshay Kumar's Khiladi 786 passes the test] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121220175208/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/BO-Report-Akshay-Kumar-s-Khiladi-786-passes-the-test/Article1-971496.aspx |date=20 December 2012 }}. Hindustan Times (11 December 2012). Retrieved 11 June 2013.</ref>\n\nAsin did not appear in any movie in 2013 or 2014. Her only movie release of 2015 was ''[[All Is Well (2015 film)|All Is Well]]'', directed by [[Umesh Shukla]] and produced by [[Bhushan Kumar]]. In one interview, director Umesh Shukla stated that Asin would be seen in an \"important dramatic role\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/asin-to-romance-abhishek-bachchan-in-mere-apne/1152793/?SocialMedia |title=Asin to romance Abhishek Bachchan in Mere Apne |work=The Indian Express |date=8 August 2013 |accessdate=19 October 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Other work==\n\n===Humanitarian work===\nDuring the shoot of her film ''Ready'' in [[Sri Lanka]], she was part of camps that were meant to help the [[Sri Lankan Tamil people]] who were affected by the [[Sri Lankan Civil War]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-07-13/news-interviews/28277165_1_eye-camp-vavuniya-lankan-president |title=Asin wins hearts in Sri Lanka&nbsp;\u2014 Times of India |work=The Times of India |date=13 July 2010 |accessdate=23 March 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn an interview during the [[Daily News and Analysis|DNA]] I Can Women's Half Marathon in 2012, Asin, speaking about the importance of health and the necessity of education said: {{bquote|\"This cause is probably one of the biggest women-centric issues in our country. I support the education of six children each year, five of which are girls. I have closely worked with these children and I know that if given the opportunity, women can educate themselves much better and know what is wrong or right for them. Education is a basic right and women should not be deprived of that.\"<ref>[http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report_health-is-of-utmost-importance-says-asin_1652424 Health is of utmost importance, says Asin]. DNA (20 February 2012). Retrieved 10 July 2012.</ref>}}\n\n===Brand ambassador===\nAsin has been the brand ambassador for several companies and products, and has appeared in commercials for [[Avon Products|Avon]],<ref>{{cite news| url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2014-02-03/news/46962966_1_brand-ambassador-avon-asin | work=The Times Of India | title=Avon signs Asin as brand ambassador in India | date=3 February 2014}}</ref> [[Mirinda]],<ref name=\"Indian Express 24 May 2009\">{{cite web|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/-I-m-a-people-s-person-/464909 |title='I'm a people's person' |work=The Indian Express |date=24 May 2009 |accessdate=16 August 2013}}</ref> [[Colgate (toothpaste)|Colgate]],<ref name=\"Indian Express 24 May 2009\" /> Fairever,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/todays-paper/tp-marketing/cavinkare-to-focus-on-nonsouth-markets/article991390.ece?ref=archive |title=CavinKare to focus on non-South markets |work=Business Line |date=11 May 2010 |accessdate=16 August 2013}}</ref> [[Tanishq]],<ref name=\"Indian Express 24 May 2009\" /> [[Big Bazaar]],<ref>{{cite news|author=Rachel Fernandes |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-05-22/news-interviews/28158100_1_asin-s-homepage-fashion-line-big-bazaar |title=Asin endorses Big Bazaar - Times of India |work=The Times of India |date=22 May 2009 |accessdate=16 August 2013}}</ref> [[Parachute (brand)|Parachute]],<ref name=\"DNA India 16 August 2013\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/1021429/report-aamir-s-find-asin |title=Aamir's find: Asin - Entertainment - DNA |work=Daily News and Analysis |accessdate=16 August 2013}}</ref> Spinz talc,<ref name=\"DNA India 16 August 2013\" /> [[Lux]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/asin-thottumkal-to-endorse-new-lux-soap-news-bollywood-kkguCCcdjef.html |title=Asin Thottumkal to endorse new Lux soap |publisher=Sify.com |date=17 September 2010 |accessdate=16 August 2013}}</ref> Amrutanjan Healthcare,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/todays-paper/tp-corporate/amrutanjan-in-talks-to-buy-beverages-co/article1003849.ece?ref=archive |title=Amrutanjan in talks to buy beverages co |work=Business Line |date=13 September 2010 |accessdate=16 August 2013}}</ref> and Clinic All Clear.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-06-18/news-interviews/28191678_1_asin-shilpa-shetty-dandruff |title=Bollywood Divas say no... - Times of India |work=The Times of India |date=18 June 2009 |accessdate=16 August 2013}}</ref> Asin has been endorsing Mirinda soft drinks since 2004.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-columns/quick-five-asin-qualitative-visibility/article5709536.ece | location=Chennai, India | work=The Hindu | first=Nandini D. | last=Tripathy | title=Quick Five: Asin - Qualitative visibility | date=20 February 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nAsin is a [[Catholic Christian]] belonging to the [[Syro-Malabar]] rite,<ref>{{cite web |author1=[[D. B. S. Jeyaraj]] |title=Indian Actress Asin Who was \u201cBlack listed\u201d by Tamil Cinema for Being Sri Lanka Friendly Weds Rahul in Grand Style |url=http://dbsjeyaraj.com/dbsj/archives/44920 |accessdate=15 March 2020 |language=English |date=5 February 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"MSN2016\">{{cite web |title=All you want to know about Asin-Rahul wedding |url=https://www.msn.com/en-in/entertainment/gallery/all-you-want-to-know-about-asin-rahul-wedding/ss-BBobiaS |publisher=[[MSN]] |accessdate=15 March 2020 |language=English |date=19 January 2016}}</ref> and currently resides in [[Mumbai]].<ref>{{cite news|author=Mehul S Thakkar |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-08-05/news-interviews/33036071_1_asin-sridevi-and-tabu-new-neighbour |title=Prabhudheva is Asin's new neighbour |work=The Times of India |date=5 August 2012 |accessdate=26 October 2012}}</ref> She also owns an apartment in [[Marine Drive, Kochi]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report_birthday-girl-asin-gifts-herself-a-plush-6-room-home_1603547 |title=Birthday girl Asin gifts herself a plush 6-room home \u2013 Entertainment \u2013 DNA |work=Daily News and Analysis |date=26 October 2011 |accessdate=26 October 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/asin-the-cool-chameleon-news-tamil-llbnxDeacia.html |title=Asin \u2013 The cool chameleon! |publisher=Sify.com |date=2 November 2011 |accessdate=26 October 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://daily.bhaskar.com/article/ENT-birthday-girl-asin-gifts-herself-a-plush-apartment-2525405.html |title=Birthday girl Asin gifts herself a plush apartment |publisher=daily.bhaskar.com |date=26 October 2011 |accessdate=26 October 2012}}</ref> and a farmhouse in [[Vagamon]], Kerala.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news-and-interviews/Asins-summer-getaway-is-her-quaint-farmhouse-in-Vagamon/articleshow/33065037.cms | work=The Times Of India | title=Asin's summer getaway is her quaint farmhouse in Vagamon - The Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.asianage.com/bollywood/asin-owns-little-piece-heaven-502 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-04-14 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140415004459/http://www.asianage.com/bollywood/asin-owns-little-piece-heaven-502 |archivedate=15 April 2014 |df=dmy }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/asins-little-piece-of-heaven-down-south-hindi-news-105992|title=Asin's 'little piece of heaven' down south|work=indiaglitz.com}}</ref> The actress is a [[Polyglotism|polyglot]]. She can speak seven languages; being well-versed in [[Malayalam]] (her [[mother tongue]]), [[Tamil language|Tamil]], [[Telugu language|Telugu]], [[Sanskrit]], English, [[Hindi]] and [[French language|French]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.asianage.com/bollywood/asin-s-jack-all-and-master-one-251 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180108104725/http://www.asianage.com/bollywood/asin-s-jack-all-and-master-one-251 |url-status=dead |archive-date=8 January 2018 |title=Asin's Jack of all and master of one |publisher=Asianage |date=3 November 2012 |accessdate=3 November 2012 }}</ref> Asin also speaks a smattering of [[Italian language|Italian]]<ref name=\"Italian\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-asin-thottumkal-knows-seven-languages-1970789|title=Asin Thottumkal knows seven languages!|work=dna}}</ref> and learnt basic [[Marathi language|Marathi]] for her movie ''[[Khiladi 786]]'', in which she played a typical Marathi girl.<ref>{{cite web|author= DC chennai |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/channels/showbiz/bollywood/asin-learns-marathi-695 |title=Asin learns Marathi |work=Deccan Chronicle |date=27 August 2012 |accessdate=26 October 2012}}</ref> In June 2013, it was reported in the Indian media that Asin was learning [[German language|German]] during her free time.<ref name=\"Desimartini.com\" /> She began learning [[Spanish language|Spanish]] after visiting Spain in early 2014.<ref name=\"Italian\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/asin-learning-spanish/1/351553.html|title=Asin learning Spanish|work=intoday.in}}</ref>\n\nAsin married Micromax co-founder [[Rahul Sharma (businessman)|Rahul Sharma]] in January 2016 in a [[Christian views on marriage|Christian wedding]] that was followed by a Hindu ceremony,<ref name=\"MSN2016\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Asin-marries-Rahul-Sharma/articleshow/50638812.cms|title=Asin Marries Rahul Sharma|accessdate=20 January 2016}}</ref> and quit acting after marriage.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-asin-quits-acting-after-marriage-other-actresses-who-chose-family-over-career-2199087|title=Asin quits acting after marriage: Other actresses who chose family over career |work=Daily News & Analysis|date=2016-04-06|language=|access-date=2016-05-02}}</ref> Their first child, a daughter Arin, was born on 24 October 2017.<ref name=\"ndtv\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/akshay-kumar-shares-first-pic-of-asin-and-rahul-sharmas-daughter-1766885|title=Akshay Kumar Shares First Pic Of Asin And Rahul Sharma's Daughter\n|website=NDTV|date=25 October 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"ndtv2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/asins-daughter-arin-18-months-old-is-the-cutest-ballerina-ever-2027890|title=Asin's Daughter Arin, 18-Months-Old, Is The Cutest Ballerina Ever|website=NDTV|date=24 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\n{{main|List of awards and nominations received by Asin }}\n\n==Filmography== \n{{BLP sources section|date=August 2018}}\n<!--References support film and role, but often do not support the award -->\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Key\n| style=\"background:#ffc;\"| {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}\n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n!scope=\"col\"| Year\n!scope=\"col\"| Title\n!scope=\"col\"| Role\n!scope=\"col\"| Language \n!scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n! class=\"unsortable\" | {{Tooltip|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| 2001\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Narendran Makan Jayakanthan Vaka]]''\n| Swathi\n|[[Malayalam]]  \n| 